HONG KONG, Nov. 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Hang Seng Tech Index gained over 3 percent during Tuesday's morning trading by opening higher at 6463.03 points, up from 6279.39 points. The index, which represents the 30 largest technology companies listed in Hong Kong, touched 6532.05 points during the morning session, marking a rebound after a declining streak from 6754.34 points logged on Oct. 22. Bilibili, a popular video streaming and sharing platform in China, led the charge by jumping 9 percent, followed by top performers including Hua Hong Semiconductor and Kuaishou, a short video app. The broader Hang Seng Index opened 1.81 percent higher to 25,609.01 points. Enditem